This paper discusses the dynamics of social contagion on social media platforms, which falls under the category of social computing and human-computer interaction. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses the visibility and attention of information, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). Finally, the paper also discusses the feedback provided to users, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
